1280B 101st Legislative Session 1280
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1280
AMENDME NT 1280B
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Jorgenson
This bill has been extensively amended (hoghoused) and may no longer be consistent with the original
intention of the sponsor.
1 An Act to prohibit drone surveillance of state military installations, to provide a
2 penalty therefor, and to authorize law enforcement to intercept or disable any
3 drone or small unmanned aircraft threatening public safety increase penalties
4 for the operation of drones over certain facilities and to provide for mitigation
5 techniques and countermeasures.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
7 Section 1. That § 50-15-3 be AMENDED:
8 50-15-3. No person may operate a drone over the grounds of a prison, correctional
9 facility, jail, juvenile detention facility, or any military facility unless expressly authorized
10 by the administrator thereof. A violation of this section is a Class 1 misdemeanor 6 felony.
11 Law enforcement officers may utilize mitigation techniques and countermeasures,
12 authorized in accordance with section 2 of this Act, in response to a violation of this
13 section.
14 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 50-15:
15 The Department of Public Safety may promulgate rules, in accordance with chapter
16 1-26, to:
17 (1) Identify the nature and scope of mitigation techniques and drone countermeasures
18 that may be utilized in response to a violation of § 50-15-3; and
19 (2) Develop and implement a training program for law enforcement officers in the
20 selection and use of mitigation techniques and drone countermeasures.
21
22
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

